HEADWORD: Brickle
<hw>Bric"kle</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>brekil</ets>, <ets>brokel</ets>, <ets>bruchel</ets>, fr. AS.
<ets>brecan</ets>, E. <ets>break</ets>. Cf. <er>Brittle</er>.]</ety>
<def>Brittle; easily broken.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As stubborn steel excels the <qex>brickle</qex> glass.</q>
<rj><qau>Turbervile.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brickleness</ent>⟦br⟧
